node.text:
Here’s the truth about “FDA Approved”:

There’s a BIG misconception that the FDA diligently reviews and approves new ingredients before we start eating them. 

Sadly this isn’t the case. 

New ingredients are usually approved by the food manufacturer themselves, and NOT by the FDA. 

All an ingredient manufacturer has to do is HIRE THEIR OWN EXPERTS to claim it’s safe. This is the green light to start adding it to food products.

Several “FDA Approved” products have been yanked from the shelves after they were found to be downright dangerous. 

But this doesn’t happen overnight. 

History shows that it takes YEARS before the FDA acts and removes harmful products from the market. 

Something very serious needs to happen – like deaths – before the FDA takes action. And even then, they may not.

Remember how Johnson & Johnson’s talc powder was recently removed from the shelves after slews of cancer claims and cover-ups by the company?

Well, the FDA didn’t ban it. 

J&J voluntarily decided to stop selling it to stop lawsuits from piling up.

Meanwhile, this controversial ingredient is banned in Europe. 

This just goes to show how little the FDA has done to protect our health. 

Tag your friends below to spread the word!

Even though we’ve made tremendous progress…the truth is that big companies just don’t change fast enough.

I believe we deserve to live in a world where our products can be made without weird – and nasty – ingredients.

Is that too much to ask?

Apparently so. Because we are so far away it’s crazy.

So, I decided to take matters into my own hands.

I launched @truvani and we have one main goal: eliminate nasty ingredients from all daily-use products.

We started with supplements. Now we are creating personal care products. 

Visit Truvani.com to learn more.

I know you’ll like them. And when you see the ingredient labels, you’ll LOVE THEM.

node.text:
I get a lot of heat when I talk about this, but…here’s the truth about Veggie Straws. 

I know the fact that they have “Veggie” in the name makes it sound good for you, but it’s a sham.

✔️Veggie Straws are really just chips. 

✔️Just like potato chips, they are mostly made from conventional potatoes and fried in vegetable oils. 

✔️Even the organic version found at Costco (swipe left to see them) is processed corn and potato flour fried in unhealthy refined oils. 

✔️These oils are not healthy for the body because they are very high in Omega 6 fatty acids, which leads to inflammation. Munching on low quality foods like this has led millions of Americans to diseases like obesity, heart disease, diabetes and cancer.

✔️The “spinach powder” and “beetroot powder” in veggie chips are really just tiny amounts of vegetable powders added, which primarily add color to the chips. This doesn’t make the product any healthier, just prettier. 

These are marketed as a healthy alternative to chips, and many daycares and schools serve these. We need to get the word out. 

Please tag your friends below and share this to your story to spread the truth! 

If you’re looking for healthy snacks - I’ll post a link in my bio with over 100 packaged snacks made without refined flours and sugars.

Tag all the parents you know! It’s back to school time and a lot of kids will have these in their lunchbox. 

There are three types of refined sugar added to Nabisco’s Fig Newtons: regular sugar, corn syrup, and invert sugar. All of these refined sugars are associated with obesity, heart disease, cancer, dementia, and liver damage. You’ll eat 8 grams of added sugar in just two small Fig Newtons. And how many of us can stop at just two cookies?

It's also made with canola oil - a heavily refined oil that goes through an insane amount of processing with chemical solvents (like hexane, a neurotoxin), steamers, neutralizers, de-waxers, bleach, and deodorizers. 

I’m not picking on Fig Newtons. (Well, maybe just a little.) I’m calling out these cookies because they market themselves as a healthier alternative. If Fig Newtons are this bad, just imagine what an “unhealthy” cookie is like.

Fig Newtons are an example of the Big Food industry at work. These corporations are really good at selling us fake food, produced in giant factories from a long list of already highly processed ingredients. They sell us these products because they are highly profitable, even if it means we’re consuming dangerous chemicals, additives, and toxic ingredients.

Good News: 

You can make “Fig Newtons” at home with good ingredients. And they’re just as chewy and satisfying as the original. Even better, actually.

Here’s a reminder of what “FDA approval” really means. How can we trust the FDA when they approve substances like this?

❌ ARTIFICIAL COLORS: Dyes derived from petroleum, linked to allergies and hyperactivity in children, which require a warning label in Europe. May also be contaminated with carcinogens, such as benzidine. 
 
❌ SODIUM NITRITE: Preservative strongly linked to cancer and heart disease.
 
❌ POTASSIUM SORBATE: Preservative shown to be genotoxic to white blood cells, which could lead to cancer.
 
❌ TBHQ: Shown to harm the immune system and to increase the risk of food allergies to nuts, milk, eggs, wheat, and shellfish.

❌ SODIUM PHOSPHATE: Can lead to excessive levels of phosphate in the blood and puts you at risk of chronic kidney disease, increased mortality, heart disease, and accelerated aging. 

❌ SUCRALOSE: Artificial sweetener linked to leukemia and other blood cancers.

❌ CARRAGEENAN: A thickener and emulsifier linked to digestive issues and cancer.

❌ DATEM & MONO AND DIGLYCERIDES: Contains trans fat which is strongly correlated with an increased risk of type 2 diabetes and heart disease.

❌ BHA & BHT: Risky preservatives linked to cancer and banned in other countries.

❌ SODIUM BENZOATE: A synthetic preservative that when combined with either ascorbic acid (vitamin C) or erythorbic acid it produces benzene, a known carcinogen. 

❌ ASPARTAME: Artificial sweetener linked to increased risk of brain tumors, lymphomas, leukemia and heart disease.

Everyone needs to know this information. Please tag your friends below and share this post to your story. You never know who it might help!

node.text:
Want to know what really opened up my eyes to how food companies exploit us? I spent years investigating the differences between European and American food products, and what I found disgusted me.

A college buddy of mine decided to go live in London for a few years. While she was there, I often had her go to Tesco and European grocery stores to take pictures of the ingredient lists for me and send me boxes of products. I’d compare them with the same brand of American products side-by-side and saw completely different ingredient lists.

In other countries you’ll find…

✔️McDonald’s french fries without dimethylpolysiloxane.
✔️Mountain Dew without Yellow #5.
✔️Heinz Ketchup without high fructose corn syrup.
✔️Pop Tarts without TBHQ and artificial colors.
✔️Activia Yogurt without carrageenan.
✔️Kellogg’s Fruit Loops without artificial colors and BHT

You see, the U.S. food system allows companies to poison us for profit with risky additives that are banned or heavily restricted overseas. 

The FDA allows Big Food to largely police itself, deciding which ingredients, chemicals, and additives are “safe.” This is a terrible policy because it leads to Americans consuming many of the very same additives and chemicals that are restricted in food in other developed countries. 

Make sure to SHARE THIS by tagging friends or sharing this to your story. This is how we put pressure on these companies to change. We’ve inspired companies like Kraft and Quaker to give us the same products they sell overseas, and we can do it again!

node.text:
Every day I eat salad. I love it. And I love how I feel when I eat an abundance of fresh greens and raw vegetables. It’s life changing! To keep it interesting and tasty, I like to mix and match a variety of different ingredients.

Here are my tips for amazing salads:

✔️ Mix in a variety of textures and flavors like crunchy, sweet, creamy, juicy, chewy, and sour into your salads. Use this chart as a guide! 

✔️ Toss in some fresh parsley, cilantro, basil, mint (or any fresh herb you like).

✔️ Rub a peeled clove of garlic all around the inside of your salad bowl before filling it up to give your whole salad a garlicky flavor that isn’t overpowering.

✔️ Choose a nice wide and shallow bowl to eat out of that gives you plenty of room to toss your salad around while you’re eating.

✔️It’s ridiculously easy and so much tastier to make your own dressings. A basic dressing can be made with oil and vinegars (balsamic, apple cider), and you can stir in some plain yogurt or mustard to make it creamy. 

I hope these tips help you make mouthwatering salads that you look forward to every day! Save this pic to your phone for inspiration.

If you feel like you don’t have the power to get food companies to drop nasty chemical ingredients from their food, I have news for you! Every time you share the truth about food products with your friends you are making a huge difference. Food companies are listening and they are changing. 

Years ago, I called Ghirardelli out for using the controversial conservative TBHQ in their chocolate squares, which has been shown to harm the immune system and is linked to other health issues, such as increasing the risk of food allergies to nuts, milk, eggs, wheat, and shellfish.

Ghirardelli recently replaced TBHQ with “extracts of oregano, flaxseed, plum, and green tea”. They also removed artificial flavors and several preservatives. 

I believe this never would have happened had we not shared the truth about their products and raised awareness!

Three more brands who have recently changed, after I wrote about them in Feeding You Lies: 

1. Pepsico removed brominated vegetable oil (BVO) from Mountain Dew. This ingredient is BANNED in Europe, which is why they sold it in other countries without it for years. 

2. Kellogg’s dropped the controversial preservative BHT (which is linked to cancer) from Frosted Flakes, so it’s now like the version they sell in other countries.

3. Quaker removed the artificial colors from their instant oatmeals and now use real fruit. 

So, keep sharing the truth about our food.

We are making a real difference! The #FoodBabeArmy is AMAZING. I love you all so much.

P.S. Ghirardelli still uses corn syrup and natural flavors - and they are not organic - so this isn’t a brand that I personally buy. My favorite chocolate brands are Hu and Alter Eco.

This is one of the tricky food labels that I discuss in my book, Food Babe Kitchen. 

“Multigrain” sounds healthy, but probably doesn’t mean what you think it does.

This simply means that multiple types of grains are used in the product. These grains may be refined into a flour, and therefore stripped of their nutrients and healthy fiber.

Like most breads, Nature’s Own Multigrain Bread is mostly made with refined wheat flour, sugar, and unhealthy soybean oil. 

These ingredients increase inflammation in the body, which can lead to obesity, heart disease, type 2 diabetes, and other diseases over time.

Since it’s not organic, it potentially contains residues of synthetic pesticides like glyphosate (Roundup). This weed killer is strongly linked to cancer. 

So, how do you choose healthy bread? Check out the last post in my feed for my favorite brands and some tips for choosing good brands.

It’s time to talk about one of the most wonderful and satisfying foods on earth – Bread! I don’t want to live without it and you shouldn’t have to either.

My diet consists mostly of plants like fruits, vegetables, seeds, beans and nuts...and I like bread on occasion, but only if it’s organic and made with nutrient-dense whole grains, sprouts, and seeds.

Swipe left to see more of my picks! 

Here’s what you need to know about conventional bread: 

✔️Wheat is commonly sprayed with Roundup weed killer at harvest - a chemical strongly linked to cancer. This practice is banned on organic crops.

✔️When conventional wheat is turned into flour, it can be treated with any of the 60 different chemicals approved by the FDA before it ends up on store shelves – including chemical bleach! This industrial processing destroys nutrients, such as Vitamin E and fiber.

✔️Wheat crops in this country have been through some serious manipulation to make them profitable for the food industry and less healthy for us.

✔️Most store bought breads are full of ingredients that are not food, like dough conditioners and preservatives. It only takes 4 ingredients to make bread – flour, yeast, water and salt, there’s really no need for all that other nonsense.
